&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit Band 5 Registered Nurses to our surgical, medical and rehabilitation wards:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;For more information and contact details please access the specialty leaflets on the right side of this page.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For joining our team we are offering:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relocation Expenses Option (T&amp;Cs apply)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supernumerary Induction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Planned Development Programme relevant to your experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rotation Programme optional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated, enthusiastic and compassionate registered nurses to join our teams. In return for your commitment, we offer excellent training and support and opportunities for career progression in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire NHS Trust is one of the UK’s leading teaching hospital Trusts, providing acute and specialist services to a population of over 1 million. In addition to being a Major Trauma Centre, we have a strong reputation for innovation, teaching and high-quality patient care, and our vision is to be a national and international leader in healthcare. Our values-driven organisational development programme; &lt;em&gt;Together Towards World Class, &lt;/em&gt;and our five-year partnership with the Virginia Mason Institute are key to us achieving this vision focussing on improving services via lean methodology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
